The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Australia research booster

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 (From left) Assocham president Anil K. Aggarwal, Union commerce minister Kamal Nath, Australian Premier John Howard and Ficci president Saroj K. Poddar at a conference organised jointly by CII, Ficci and Assocham in New Delhi on Monday. (PTI)

 New Delhi, March 6: Australian Premier John Howard today announced an Aus $25-million research assistance to India to foster co-operation in science and technology. He said the two countries would sign a memorandum of understanding to boost research co-operation in biotechnology.

 He was addressing the captains of Indian industry at a conference jointly organised by the Confederation of Indian Industry, Federation of Indian Chambers of Commerce and Industry (Ficci) and Assocham.

 Stating that Australia has become a favourite destination both among Indian tourists and the entertainment industry, he said, To facilitate this growth, I am pleased to announce that the Australian government will allow Indian citizens to access our tourist e-visa scheme. 




